T14	p 875 1267	L. capsica is a member of Liberibacter, a bacterial genus responsible for the destruction of commercially significant crops. Three species belonging to Liberibacter, for instance, are linked to Huanglongbing, or citrus greening. The disease is spread by small insects called psyllids and is a major threat to the citrus industry worldwide. Unfortunately, there exists no cure for the disease.
